WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:01.656
<i>male announcer:
Previously on "Dominion"...</i>

00:01.690 --> 00:03.078
I'm sending soldiers
across the trench

00:03.113 --> 00:04.494
as soon as you
drive out of here.

00:04.529 --> 00:07.791
Surrender, Zoe,
and everything changes.

00:07.826 --> 00:09.313
Sniper!

00:09.348 --> 00:10.660
[gunfire]

00:10.695 --> 00:12.995
Claire. Claire.

00:13.031 --> 00:14.664
<i>The added stress of surgery</i>

00:14.699 --> 00:17.183
<i>caused a spontaneous
miscarriage.</i>

00:17.218 --> 00:19.835
All you had to do was kill
Claire Riesen... you failed.

00:19.871 --> 00:22.204
What if I were to tell you
I could make you a dyad like me.

00:22.256 --> 00:25.791
Once possessed, the body
stops aging, stops dying.

00:25.793 --> 00:28.044
Your life isn't over,
General.

00:28.096 --> 00:30.546
<i>And neither was the angel
that you loved.</i>

00:30.598 --> 00:34.300
You've spoiled me into
almost believing I'm human.

00:34.302 --> 00:36.185
Clementine?

00:36.220 --> 00:39.021
- I've missed you so much.
- I'm not leaving you again.

00:39.057 --> 00:41.223
Then we'll both die
and Vega will be lost.

00:41.275 --> 00:43.976
I don't believe in Alex,
Michael.

00:43.978 --> 00:46.812
But you do. Protect him.

00:46.814 --> 00:48.230
I can't change
what you did for me, Noma.

00:48.282 --> 00:49.815
We need to get to Vega.

00:49.817 --> 00:51.317
[snarling]

00:55.239 --> 00:56.455
Shit.

00:59.410 --> 01:03.162
[growling, snarling]

01:05.667 --> 01:07.049
Weapons?

01:07.085 --> 01:08.668
Slim Jims, AA batteries.

01:08.670 --> 01:11.337
We definitely should have
holed up in a gun store.

01:14.809 --> 01:15.975
Please tell me
you have a plan.

01:16.010 --> 01:16.976
I got nothing.

01:17.011 --> 01:18.944
Then we fight.

01:18.980 --> 01:20.513
Okay.

01:27.121 --> 01:29.021
[snarling, speaking foreign language]
_

01:29.023 --> 01:31.607
[chainsaw revs]

01:35.548 --> 01:37.417
_

01:38.866 --> 01:40.966
You're late.

01:42.000 --> 01:48.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:51.713 --> 01:54.680
Noma.
Your wounds... are they...

01:54.716 --> 01:58.267
- Alex sewed me up. I'm okay.
- Is Gabriel dead?

01:58.302 --> 01:59.802
Gabriel's captive
in New Delphi.

01:59.854 --> 02:01.520
- He's alive?
- Gabriel sacrificed himself

02:01.556 --> 02:03.055
so that I could escape
and get to you.

02:03.091 --> 02:04.640
Doesn't sound like
Gabriel.

02:04.692 --> 02:06.609
- Gabriel's full of surprises.
- And Julian?

02:06.644 --> 02:09.995
Soon he'll raise his army
and attack Vega... that's clear.

02:10.031 --> 02:11.497
The city doesn't have much time.

02:11.532 --> 02:13.365
We need to get going.

02:21.242 --> 02:24.960
<i>[ominous music]</i>

02:24.996 --> 02:29.298
<i>♪
♪</i>

02:29.333 --> 02:32.468
<i>There's no entry.</i>

02:32.503 --> 02:35.254
For me, there is.

02:35.289 --> 02:38.591
I'm William Whele.

02:41.512 --> 02:43.679
<i>Smell that?</i>

02:43.731 --> 02:45.347
Did you sleep here?

02:45.399 --> 02:47.399
Yeah.

02:47.435 --> 02:51.320
Eight-balls, destroyed
before they reached the house.

02:51.355 --> 02:54.190
It's like someone
was protecting you.

02:54.242 --> 02:57.660
They were burned
from the inside out.

02:57.695 --> 02:59.345
I've seen this before.

02:59.380 --> 03:00.329
When?

03:00.364 --> 03:04.116
[screaming]

03:06.420 --> 03:09.288
Recently.

03:15.630 --> 03:17.463
Tell me, David.

03:17.465 --> 03:20.049
How long before I'm the one
who's dodging bullets?

03:20.101 --> 03:22.718
Now why would I kill
a pretty girl like you?

03:22.770 --> 03:24.970
<i>You know I like
our little chats.</i>

03:24.972 --> 03:26.806
I don't want to be sinning
more than you do.

03:26.808 --> 03:30.476
But we agreed to let Claire and
Zoe's negotiations play out.

03:30.478 --> 03:33.445
Let the war end when it's
just heating up? Not a chance.

03:33.481 --> 03:35.614
<i>An opportunity
presented itself.</i>

03:35.650 --> 03:38.484
Do you expect to continue
receiving my help?

03:38.486 --> 03:40.536
Arika,
we're not partners,

03:40.571 --> 03:43.239
and I don't work for you,
so let's be clear.

03:43.291 --> 03:46.909
When this war is over,
I'm going to control Vega.

03:46.961 --> 03:48.494
Not today.

03:48.496 --> 03:51.497
But soon, with or without
your help.

03:54.635 --> 03:56.669
Hello, David.

03:59.423 --> 04:01.473
Hello, Zoe.

04:03.110 --> 04:05.311
David?

04:05.346 --> 04:06.645
<i>David?</i>

04:06.681 --> 04:08.397
<i>Are you still there?</i>

04:08.432 --> 04:10.516
<i>I can't hear you.</i>

04:10.518 --> 04:13.419
<i>David.</i>

04:13.454 --> 04:16.422
[dramatic music]

04:16.457 --> 04:18.341
♪ ♪

04:18.375 --> 04:23.376
Sync and corrections by explosiveskull
www.addic7ed.com

04:24.699 --> 04:27.583
- Who's Arika?
- Claire's right hand.

04:27.618 --> 04:30.419
She wanted her identity
kept secret but, uh,

04:30.454 --> 04:32.788
Arika is a valuable asset.

04:32.840 --> 04:35.925
Pearson was your asset too,
but I just watched him die.

04:35.960 --> 04:38.961
Bringing us to the law
of unintended consequences.

04:39.013 --> 04:39.962
Meaning?

04:40.014 --> 04:42.381
Come on, boys.

04:42.383 --> 04:43.883
Pearson's men weren't very happy

04:43.885 --> 04:47.136
with the way you terminated
his services.

04:47.188 --> 04:49.805
They work for me now.
They're not the only ones.

04:49.857 --> 04:51.774
You've been at this
for a couple of months.

04:51.809 --> 04:53.859
I ran an underground
for 20 years.

04:53.895 --> 04:55.527
I know enough to know that
trying to kill Claire Riesen

04:55.563 --> 04:57.029
wasn't just a mistake.

04:57.064 --> 04:59.481
It destroyed any chance
we have for peace.

04:59.533 --> 05:01.650
Peace is not the answer.

05:01.702 --> 05:04.954
The V-6s are too entrenched
and too powerful,

05:04.989 --> 05:09.158
and they will use that power to
stop you by any means necessary.

05:09.210 --> 05:13.913
The only chance for revolution
is to burn them down.

05:13.915 --> 05:17.583
Now why don't we
set our differences aside

05:17.585 --> 05:19.802
till the war is won?

05:19.837 --> 05:21.553
For now, Whele.

05:23.174 --> 05:26.842
But when it's over,
one of us is going to die.

05:26.894 --> 05:29.094
Ladies first.

05:35.903 --> 05:38.604
<i>Make sure to get
some rest now.</i>

05:38.606 --> 05:41.106
<i>Claire, I'm so sorry.</i>

05:41.108 --> 05:45.511
Had I known about the meeting
with Zoe... if I'd been there...

05:45.546 --> 05:48.530
the cowards responsible
for this will pay.

05:53.287 --> 05:55.871
Could you give us
the room, please?

05:55.923 --> 05:58.874
Just for a moment.

05:58.926 --> 06:01.427
If you need anything
at all...

06:10.104 --> 06:11.637
<i>[door closes]</i>

06:11.672 --> 06:14.223
We need to give Zoe
the war that she deserves.

06:14.275 --> 06:17.393
Strike hard, strike fast.

06:17.445 --> 06:19.028
Destroy this rebellion
once and for all

06:19.063 --> 06:21.647
before it gets even more
out of control.

06:25.987 --> 06:28.120
I want the helicopter ready
at a moment's notice.

06:28.155 --> 06:29.722
What's wrong?

06:29.757 --> 06:31.290
Gates isn't as good a liar
as he thinks.

06:31.325 --> 06:32.708
He's up to something.

06:32.743 --> 06:35.577
- Then go now.
- No.

06:35.629 --> 06:36.996
Claire's loss is unfortunate,

06:36.998 --> 06:38.747
but it's also
a stroke of good luck.

06:38.799 --> 06:40.716
<i>She'll fight back
harder than ever,</i>

06:40.751 --> 06:44.003
and we'll build a new Helena
out of what's left of Vega.

06:44.005 --> 06:45.771
But if Gates suspects us,
he'll tell Claire.

06:45.806 --> 06:48.007
You're right.
One way or another,

06:48.009 --> 06:51.010
Gates Foley is a problem
that needs solving.

06:55.016 --> 06:57.733
You're nothing but another
of Julian's sick jokes.

06:57.768 --> 07:00.436
Edward, it really is me.
Clementine.

07:00.488 --> 07:03.906
You tell Julian that I will
never reveal the location

07:03.941 --> 07:05.190
of the Amphora.

07:05.192 --> 07:08.193
You shouldn't be
so eager to die.

07:08.195 --> 07:10.079
Leave me alone.

07:10.114 --> 07:11.997
Alex killed me.

07:12.033 --> 07:14.533
He evicted my soul,
ripped it from my body.

07:14.535 --> 07:17.119
And our daughter watched.

07:17.171 --> 07:20.756
Julian brought me back.

07:20.791 --> 07:23.042
Remember, Edward?

07:23.044 --> 07:25.978
I used to dream about a place
where we could live in peace.

07:26.013 --> 07:29.431
Tell Julian what he wants and
we'll be husband and wife again.

07:29.467 --> 07:30.799
You were never my wife.

07:30.851 --> 07:32.851
She was your wife
for nine years.

07:32.887 --> 07:36.055
I loved you for 25.

07:36.057 --> 07:37.890
I remember the day we met.

07:37.892 --> 07:41.226
The world was crumbling, but
you weren't afraid of anything.

07:41.228 --> 07:43.896
My brave general.

07:43.898 --> 07:47.983
I'm not the man
you think I am.

07:48.035 --> 07:50.202
I never was.

07:52.406 --> 07:56.125
<i>[metallic click]</i>

07:56.160 --> 07:57.409
[click]

07:57.411 --> 07:59.828
<i>[military radio chatter]</i>

07:59.880 --> 08:01.547
<i>The books are for show,
right?</i>

08:01.582 --> 08:05.000
You civilians don't really read
that crap.

08:05.052 --> 08:06.835
Those who do not learn
from history

08:06.887 --> 08:09.471
are condemned to repeat it.

08:09.507 --> 08:11.890
Those who think that fancy
quotes make them smarter

08:11.926 --> 08:14.810
are often due to get punched
in the mouth.

08:14.845 --> 08:18.397
Numbers don't lie, and if I
can read them, anyone can.

08:18.432 --> 08:20.482
For God's sake, Foster,

08:20.518 --> 08:21.934
if you're going to sell
tri-tip out the back door

08:21.936 --> 08:23.902
at least be clever about it.

08:23.938 --> 08:27.523
You're not only a thief,
you're a bad one.

08:27.575 --> 08:29.741
[background noise]

08:29.777 --> 08:33.361
I don't like civilians.

08:33.414 --> 08:36.748
One more word about tri-tip
will result in me shoving this

08:36.784 --> 08:41.453
inventory file so far up your
ass, it'll part you hair.

08:46.127 --> 08:49.928
[coughs]

09:03.477 --> 09:07.196
[grunts]

09:07.231 --> 09:08.947
What is this?

09:08.983 --> 09:10.883
Much as I do enjoy
torturing you,

09:10.918 --> 09:16.205
I think it's time that we tried
a more targeted approach.

09:16.240 --> 09:18.290
<i>Who are your friends,
Gabriel?</i>

09:18.325 --> 09:22.161
I don't think you have a single
human or angel as your friend.

09:22.163 --> 09:24.079
Certainly not Michael.

09:24.131 --> 09:26.165
He's your twin.

09:26.167 --> 09:29.084
Any of your angelic underlings?
I think not.

09:29.136 --> 09:33.138
Where's your vaunted army
and your herald Janeck?

09:33.174 --> 09:35.257
Weren't they supposed
to be here by now?

09:35.309 --> 09:37.776
<i>On the flip side,
your enemies multiply.</i>

09:37.811 --> 09:39.678
Claire Riesen dropped a bomb
on your aerie

09:39.713 --> 09:41.747
using the Queen of Helena's
plane.

09:41.782 --> 09:43.515
We know how
the Chosen One feels,

09:43.517 --> 09:46.902
and his poor angel sidekick
would rather rip off her wings

09:46.937 --> 09:49.321
than spend another minute
in your presence.

09:49.356 --> 09:51.073
I believe that was
your company

09:51.108 --> 09:53.025
she found most
disagreeable.

09:54.695 --> 09:57.329
You're alone, Gabriel.

09:57.364 --> 10:01.333
In all the universe,
totally alone.

10:02.786 --> 10:04.336
This is worse than torture.

10:04.371 --> 10:07.873
May we please return
to the electroshock therapy?

10:07.875 --> 10:10.759
Oh, we're just
getting started.

10:10.794 --> 10:12.427
[beeping, whirring]

10:12.463 --> 10:14.880
[hums]

10:27.394 --> 10:28.810
[groans]

10:30.898 --> 10:34.483
Sweet dreams.

10:41.625 --> 10:45.240
<i>- [Claire groans]
- [radio chatter]</i>

10:45.275 --> 10:47.512
You should be in bed.

10:47.547 --> 10:49.764
I'm fine.

10:49.799 --> 10:52.267
Arika,
thank you for coming.

10:52.302 --> 10:54.802
Mr. Foley, I was surprised
to hear you wanted me.

10:54.854 --> 10:57.555
- Hmm.
- Claire, shouldn't you be resting?

10:57.557 --> 11:00.225
I am exactly
where I should be.

11:00.260 --> 11:01.893
Understood?

11:01.895 --> 11:03.461
We have five Archangel Corps
soldiers

11:03.496 --> 11:05.063
on the other side of the trench,

11:05.065 --> 11:06.481
and another strike team's
preparing to join them.

11:06.533 --> 11:08.366
Any luck tracking
Zoe or David?

11:08.401 --> 11:11.202
No, but from our soldiers'
intel we believe that we know

11:11.238 --> 11:13.571
the locations of
a number of Zoe's warlords.

11:13.573 --> 11:15.039
And if we take them out,

11:15.075 --> 11:17.075
it will be a major blow
to her support base.

11:17.077 --> 11:19.377
What do you think?

11:19.412 --> 11:23.915
If you want to stop a dog
from biting, take out its teeth.

11:23.917 --> 11:26.501
The armory.

11:26.553 --> 11:28.586
We go after the weapons,
not the people.

11:28.588 --> 11:30.688
We're gonna need those weapons
if Gabriel attacks...

11:30.724 --> 11:32.724
when Gabriel attacks.

11:32.759 --> 11:34.726
The decision is yours,
Claire.

11:36.429 --> 11:39.097
Sanders, prepare your men.

11:39.099 --> 11:42.183
We're going to raid the armory.

11:52.245 --> 11:54.829
Everything's ready.

11:54.864 --> 11:56.864
We can be back in Helena
by nightfall.

11:56.916 --> 11:58.082
Just say the word.

11:58.118 --> 11:59.951
Soon. Bring Kat in here.

11:59.953 --> 12:02.086
I need to send a message
to David.

12:02.122 --> 12:03.371
You don't trust
the radios?

12:03.423 --> 12:04.622
With Gates running
hot and cold,

12:04.624 --> 12:07.542
we need to take
every precaution.

12:07.594 --> 12:10.962
See that our friend David
gets this.

12:14.634 --> 12:17.685
<i>[pop music in background]</i>

12:17.721 --> 12:26.277
<i>♪
♪</i>

12:26.313 --> 12:27.729
We have chips.

12:31.284 --> 12:34.068
I'm a little low on cash,
but if you give me a beer,

12:34.120 --> 12:35.720
I can pay you back
in a couple of days.

12:35.755 --> 12:38.823
This is a bar, son,
not a bank.

12:42.495 --> 12:45.630
What if I told you
I used to be William Whele?

12:45.665 --> 12:48.416
[scoffs]
William Whele's dead.

12:48.468 --> 12:51.336
Not dead.
Exiled by my father.

12:51.338 --> 12:52.920
Where'd he send you,
to hell and back?

12:52.972 --> 12:54.555
Close. Arizona.

12:54.591 --> 12:57.558
[man chuckles]

12:57.594 --> 13:00.478
William Whele, huh?
Back from the dead.

13:00.513 --> 13:04.015
First angels and now ghosts.

13:04.017 --> 13:08.236
Well, I don't believe in ghosts
and, uh, I don't like liars.

13:08.271 --> 13:11.823
Well, like I was saying,
I was exiled out to the desert,

13:11.858 --> 13:13.941
given a death sentence,
but I made it back.

13:13.993 --> 13:16.994
Boy, stop bullshitting us.
I met William Whele.

13:17.030 --> 13:19.697
I shook his hand
after a sermon.

13:19.699 --> 13:22.867
They were like
a little girl's hands. Buttery.

13:22.869 --> 13:26.237
You ain't no William Whele.

13:43.223 --> 13:46.190
[groans]

14:12.001 --> 14:15.586
[breathing heavily]

14:29.102 --> 14:30.101
[crack]

14:32.272 --> 14:36.190
<i>- [laughter echoes]
- [whispering voices]</i>

14:41.414 --> 14:45.450
<i>- [laughter]
- [overlapping voices]</i>

14:58.131 --> 14:59.213
Excuse me. Let me ask you...

14:59.265 --> 15:01.933
[chokes]

15:08.391 --> 15:13.644
<i>[overlapping voices,
whispering]</i>

15:19.285 --> 15:23.321
<i>- [laughter]
- [growling]</i>

15:23.323 --> 15:25.740
<i>[snarling]</i>

15:31.297 --> 15:33.464
No use struggling.

15:33.500 --> 15:35.216
You're not in danger.

15:35.251 --> 15:37.301
I just need your help.

15:45.011 --> 15:47.011
Claire Riesen?

16:00.658 --> 16:02.324
What are you doing
in New Delphi?

16:02.376 --> 16:05.778
Shh. Julian will hear you.

16:10.501 --> 16:13.669
He did this to you?

16:13.721 --> 16:15.921
But you escaped.
Clever boy.

16:19.393 --> 16:20.726
Gabriel, let me help you.

16:20.761 --> 16:22.428
<i>Claire, wait.</i>

16:24.014 --> 16:26.014
Be careful.

16:26.066 --> 16:27.232
He's an Archangel.

16:27.268 --> 16:29.017
Noma.

16:29.069 --> 16:30.903
What are you doing here?

16:30.938 --> 16:33.322
He could be dangerous
if we unpin his wings.

16:33.357 --> 16:35.441
And you... I know you.

16:35.443 --> 16:37.910
You're the Queen of Helena,
aren't you?

16:37.945 --> 16:41.663
Julian's tortured him.
He needs our help.

16:41.699 --> 16:44.450
Yes. By all means,
Claire, help me.

16:44.452 --> 16:47.002
Gabriel's mankind's
greatest enemy.

16:47.037 --> 16:50.255
He's more dangerous
than ever. Even now.

16:50.291 --> 16:52.374
But why would I harm you?

16:52.426 --> 16:55.210
Three beautiful women,
kind enough to help me

16:55.262 --> 16:57.596
in my hour of need?

16:57.631 --> 17:00.132
<i>You honestly believe that I'd
waste an ounce of energy</i>

17:00.134 --> 17:04.685
on anything other than placing
Julian's head on a pike?

17:04.722 --> 17:08.307
[women giggle]

17:08.309 --> 17:09.942
You're amused.

17:09.977 --> 17:11.810
You can't defeat Julian.

17:14.147 --> 17:17.148
- No one can.
- He's invincible.

17:17.151 --> 17:20.368
Julian will break you.
He's already breaking you.

17:20.404 --> 17:24.873
Resistance is impossible.

17:24.909 --> 17:26.791
Take these damn pins out,

17:26.827 --> 17:30.662
and I'll show you what
I can do.

17:30.664 --> 17:32.915
- He means well.
- He's hopeless.

17:32.967 --> 17:34.666
So?

17:34.668 --> 17:36.301
Should we take the pins out?

17:36.337 --> 17:39.004
Yes.

17:49.650 --> 17:51.350
[yells]

17:51.352 --> 17:53.986
[panting]

17:54.021 --> 17:55.988
Good. Good.

17:56.023 --> 17:58.690
Now the other one, please.

18:00.661 --> 18:02.694
[laughing]

18:03.781 --> 18:05.197
Better?

18:06.617 --> 18:09.167
[groans]
Yes, yes.

18:09.203 --> 18:12.754
I need time to recover...
heal.

18:12.790 --> 18:17.042
An hour, maybe two, and then
I'll summon my angels

18:17.044 --> 18:19.094
and we'll slaughter that dyad

18:19.129 --> 18:21.763
and everyone else
in this cursed pit.

18:21.799 --> 18:25.133
Of course you will.

18:25.185 --> 18:27.185
You don't believe me.

18:27.221 --> 18:30.939
No.
Even with your wings.

18:30.975 --> 18:33.058
It's a losing proposition.

18:33.060 --> 18:35.777
But I'm an Archangel.

18:35.813 --> 18:39.448
One of the greatest warriors
the heavens have ever seen.

18:39.483 --> 18:42.451
Julian is far more
powerful than that.

18:42.486 --> 18:45.904
You don't stand a chance.

18:45.906 --> 18:47.539
What do you suggest?

18:47.575 --> 18:52.327
Stay here.
With us.

18:52.379 --> 18:53.845
Why, exactly?

18:53.881 --> 18:55.747
Because
we will protect you.

18:55.749 --> 18:58.016
Because we want you.

19:04.725 --> 19:09.227
Surrender, Gabriel.
It's easy if you try.

19:17.938 --> 19:20.272
[giggling]

19:24.945 --> 19:27.746
I did have
buttery hands, didn't I?

19:27.781 --> 19:30.082
I take it as a compliment,

19:30.117 --> 19:31.867
but I don't think
you meant it that way.

19:31.919 --> 19:34.753
Get out of my way.

19:34.788 --> 19:38.340
It's amazing how our skin
changes, isn't it?

19:38.375 --> 19:41.176
The worse we treat it,
the stronger it gets.

19:41.211 --> 19:43.378
Humans are the same,
aren't they?

19:43.430 --> 19:45.931
These...

19:45.966 --> 19:48.884
hands have done things I...

19:48.936 --> 19:52.387
never thought
I'd be capable of.

19:52.439 --> 19:54.690
Hey, look man, I was
joking around in there.

19:54.725 --> 19:56.108
I'm not looking
for trouble.

19:56.143 --> 19:59.277
Neither am I.

19:59.313 --> 20:01.113
[grunting]

20:10.791 --> 20:12.708
Ah!

20:12.743 --> 20:15.627
[gasping]

20:15.663 --> 20:16.912
[crack]

20:16.964 --> 20:18.080
[spits]

20:33.480 --> 20:36.732
Edward, Clementine.

20:36.767 --> 20:38.433
I have news from Vega.

20:38.485 --> 20:40.485
I'm sorry to be the one
to tell you,

20:40.521 --> 20:43.155
but Vega has fallen
into civil war.

20:43.190 --> 20:46.358
One side is led by a former
colleague of yours, David Whele,

20:46.360 --> 20:48.493
and the other
by your daughter Claire.

20:48.529 --> 20:51.163
And unfortunately
she's recently been shot.

20:51.198 --> 20:53.582
- No.
- <i>Edward, careful.</i>

20:53.617 --> 20:57.202
She's getting
the very best care available

20:57.204 --> 21:00.088
from what I hear.

21:00.124 --> 21:01.840
Why should I believe you?

21:01.875 --> 21:03.508
<i>Well, how can you
doubt it, Edward?</i>

21:03.544 --> 21:07.129
You left an inexperienced girl
in charge of a city.

21:07.181 --> 21:11.133
Everything that you fought so
hard to build is disintegrating

21:11.185 --> 21:13.552
while you're here
dying unnecessarily

21:13.554 --> 21:15.137
a thousand miles away.

21:15.189 --> 21:18.440
<i>A dyad can help Claire
to save the city,</i>

21:18.475 --> 21:22.861
especially with a New Delphi
army and me at his side.

21:22.896 --> 21:26.398
Unlike the eight-balls...
your term, not mine...

21:26.400 --> 21:31.453
the higher angel shares control
of the body with the human soul.

21:31.488 --> 21:33.955
Symbiosis, not destruction.

21:33.991 --> 21:35.657
Dyadism.

21:35.709 --> 21:39.461
<i>You will remain Edward Riesen
in every way.</i>

21:39.496 --> 21:41.630
All it takes from you
is the Amphora.

21:41.665 --> 21:43.248
I'm not going to betray

21:43.250 --> 21:45.484
everything that
I stand for, Julian.

21:45.519 --> 21:49.838
What do you stand for,
Edward, if not your wife?

21:49.890 --> 21:52.507
And your daughter?

21:52.559 --> 21:55.177
[Edward coughs]

22:04.521 --> 22:06.071
You rat me out?

22:06.106 --> 22:08.740
What you were doing
was illegal... I did my job.

22:08.776 --> 22:11.610
I'm going to show you
what we do to rats on this base.

22:11.612 --> 22:15.614
[deafening roar]

22:15.616 --> 22:19.584
[gasping]

22:28.095 --> 22:30.762
[snarling]

22:33.884 --> 22:36.935
[speaking gutturally]

22:43.310 --> 22:45.811
Oh...

22:49.900 --> 22:52.234
All warfare
is based on deception.

22:52.286 --> 22:56.288
Picked that up from Sun Tzu
in one of my stupid books.

22:56.323 --> 23:00.992
[panting]

23:03.330 --> 23:07.666
[distant screaming]

23:20.681 --> 23:23.515
[screaming continues]

23:32.192 --> 23:34.943
[yelling gutturally]

24:00.554 --> 24:02.721
Clementine!

24:02.723 --> 24:05.307
<i>[baby cries]</i>

24:05.359 --> 24:07.058
Claire?

24:13.984 --> 24:14.950
Clementine.

24:14.985 --> 24:17.068
[murmuring]

24:24.745 --> 24:27.629
None of that changes
who you really are.

24:27.664 --> 24:30.749
I'm an imposter.
A charlatan.

24:30.751 --> 24:34.336
No, you're the man
who defended humanity.

24:34.388 --> 24:36.671
The man who
founded and ran Vega.

24:36.723 --> 24:38.423
<i>All of that's the same.</i>

24:38.425 --> 24:40.475
Doesn't matter
if those ribbons

24:40.510 --> 24:45.730
were pinned on your chest
before the war or not.

24:45.766 --> 24:47.399
You always know
what to say to me, Clem.

24:47.434 --> 24:51.736
Take the offer.
You'll be immortal, like me.

24:51.772 --> 24:54.155
What if Julian uses
the Amphora as a weapon

24:54.191 --> 24:57.359
and I can't... I can't...

24:59.112 --> 25:04.332
Are you okay? Edward?

25:04.368 --> 25:07.752
There's no time left.
You need to take his deal.

25:07.788 --> 25:10.422
Julian!

25:10.457 --> 25:11.623
Do you love me, Edward?

25:14.294 --> 25:17.345
- Yes.
- Then save yourself. For us.

25:17.381 --> 25:19.931
[coughing]

25:19.967 --> 25:23.134
Shh, shh, shh.

25:30.477 --> 25:33.061
I know better than
to ask.

25:33.113 --> 25:35.313
I'll take another.

25:41.905 --> 25:43.822
Ahh...

25:43.824 --> 25:48.326
Now where was I?

25:48.328 --> 25:50.628
Cast out to the wastelands,
that's right.

25:50.664 --> 25:54.215
I was out there for over
three months and I survived.

25:54.251 --> 25:58.803
No. I thrived.

25:58.839 --> 26:01.673
My first test came
when I was captured.

26:01.675 --> 26:03.675
<i>Eight-balls.</i>

26:03.677 --> 26:06.177
They made the best companions,

26:06.179 --> 26:08.813
unless you're into insanity
and an unending stream

26:08.849 --> 26:11.433
of sadism and cruelty.

26:11.485 --> 26:16.154
Burning, cutting,
biting torture.

26:16.189 --> 26:18.990
They fight constantly.

26:19.026 --> 26:21.693
More vicious
than you can ever imagine.

26:21.695 --> 26:23.445
[coughing]

26:23.497 --> 26:25.947
Where is Julian?

26:28.502 --> 26:31.036
- Oh, no.
- Save him.

26:31.038 --> 26:33.872
General. Listen to me.
Listen to me.

26:33.874 --> 26:36.591
Where is the Amphora?
This is your last chance.

26:36.626 --> 26:38.259
He's running out
of time.

26:38.295 --> 26:40.345
Vega needs you.
She needs you.

26:40.380 --> 26:42.764
Let me make you
what they need.

26:42.799 --> 26:44.795
Tell him, Edward!

26:48.216 --> 26:51.217
What you did for Alex
was extremely brave.

26:51.219 --> 26:52.885
<i>And rare.</i>

26:52.887 --> 26:54.387
I realize the price was great.

26:54.389 --> 26:56.940
I did what I had to.

26:56.975 --> 26:59.192
Now I need to make sure
he gets home to Vega.

26:59.227 --> 27:02.028
- And what happens then?
- I guess we'll see, won't we?

27:03.732 --> 27:07.984
Yesterday I went out to draw
the eight-balls away from Alex

27:08.036 --> 27:09.736
and something strange
happened.

27:09.738 --> 27:12.538
- What?
- A man appeared to me.

27:12.574 --> 27:17.577
There was a presence about him,
like he was something more.

27:17.579 --> 27:21.297
I was delirious, but what sticks
in my mind is, he said...

27:21.333 --> 27:24.250
Bring him east.

27:24.252 --> 27:26.886
Does it make any sense
to you?

27:26.921 --> 27:28.338
No.

27:28.390 --> 27:30.223
[engine struggles]

27:30.258 --> 27:31.924
- [engine turns]
- Ooh!

27:31.926 --> 27:33.092
Let's roll.

27:34.596 --> 27:36.813
You think your brother's
still alive?

27:36.848 --> 27:39.148
He is for now.

27:39.184 --> 27:42.352
I can't imagine
what he's going through.

27:42.404 --> 27:45.355
[rock music]

27:45.407 --> 27:54.447
♪ ♪

28:08.263 --> 28:15.768
♪ ♪

28:22.644 --> 28:24.777
Naughty, naughty.

28:24.813 --> 28:27.947
Oh, you have no idea.

28:27.982 --> 28:32.118
[ominous music]

28:32.153 --> 28:36.205
Wait. Who are you?

28:36.241 --> 28:42.245
♪ ♪

28:55.176 --> 28:57.593
Martin, you're with me
at the armory.

28:57.645 --> 29:00.563
Calderon, your team comes around
the flank to cut off a retreat.

29:00.598 --> 29:02.315
This is the first battle
of the war,

29:02.350 --> 29:03.816
and we're going to
send a message

29:03.852 --> 29:05.818
- that the whole city'll hear.
- [door opens]

29:07.605 --> 29:10.189
- What do you think you're doing?
- Assuring victory.

29:10.191 --> 29:12.775
In order to ambush Claire's
forces at the armory,

29:12.827 --> 29:14.327
you need me and my men.

29:14.362 --> 29:15.611
Don't tell me
Consul Whele

29:15.663 --> 29:17.330
wants to fight
on the front lines.

29:17.365 --> 29:19.115
Don't tell me you're
so naive to think that

29:19.167 --> 29:21.667
I would let you alone reap the
benefits of my intel from Arika.

29:21.703 --> 29:23.453
Oh, I'm not.

29:23.505 --> 29:25.788
I just didn't think you'd want
to get your hands dirty.

29:25.840 --> 29:27.540
Or rather, your hand.

29:27.542 --> 29:29.125
That is wittier than
I would have thought

29:29.177 --> 29:31.878
you were capable of.
Nice.

29:31.880 --> 29:35.882
Let's claim
the armory victory together.

29:35.884 --> 29:38.885
[suspenseful music]

29:38.887 --> 29:47.026
♪ ♪

30:07.715 --> 30:10.800
My mother taught me
how to shoot. You?

30:10.835 --> 30:12.385
Gifted amateur.

30:12.420 --> 30:14.387
Rule number one, always
keep your muzzle pointed

30:14.422 --> 30:16.756
- in a safe direction.
- I don't need instructions.

30:16.758 --> 30:18.090
Be sure of your target
and what's beyond it.

30:18.092 --> 30:19.842
Damn it, Zoe.

30:19.894 --> 30:21.511
But most important, you might
want to take the safety off

30:21.563 --> 30:23.229
if you're planning to fire it.

30:23.264 --> 30:24.897
Ah...

31:16.401 --> 31:21.404
[gunfire]

31:43.645 --> 31:46.512
Heads up.
They should be attacking soon.

31:48.316 --> 31:50.683
Gunfire at the Agri-tower.

31:50.685 --> 31:52.735
- What?
- It's the Archangel Corps.

31:52.770 --> 31:54.820
That's impossible.
Our intel was good.

31:54.856 --> 31:56.322
David Whele, master spy.

31:56.357 --> 31:57.740
Claire plans to attack
the armory.

31:57.775 --> 31:59.692
She made a fool of you, Whele.
And me.

31:59.694 --> 32:01.110
<i>The Corps aren't coming here.</i>

32:01.162 --> 32:04.330
They're too busy
taking our food supply.

32:05.500 --> 32:08.117
Damn it.

32:08.169 --> 32:10.202
This is your fault.

32:10.204 --> 32:12.171
- That's not possible.
- <i>No, it's true.</i>

32:12.206 --> 32:14.957
Claire's troops, they took
the Agri-tower instead.

32:15.009 --> 32:17.260
- No.
- And I really don't like

32:17.295 --> 32:18.544
the sound of that.

32:18.546 --> 32:20.880
Gates knows. It's a trap.

32:30.358 --> 32:31.474
[high-pitched beep]

32:52.580 --> 32:54.664
[gasps]

32:57.251 --> 32:59.418
[grunts]

33:01.339 --> 33:04.056
Help me. David.

33:09.430 --> 33:12.064
[coughs]

33:14.936 --> 33:15.901
Okay.

33:15.937 --> 33:17.436
<i>[distant shouts]</i>

33:20.108 --> 33:21.907
You were right.

33:21.943 --> 33:23.826
Only one of us
is going to survive.

33:23.861 --> 33:26.612
David. David!

33:26.614 --> 33:29.615
<i>[men shouting]</i>

33:36.422 --> 33:38.973
Oh. That hurts.

33:45.398 --> 33:47.865
What is the meaning
of this?

33:54.373 --> 33:57.241
<i>[footsteps approach]</i>

34:00.379 --> 34:02.212
Who are you?

34:02.248 --> 34:03.964
Really?

34:04.000 --> 34:05.499
<i>My, oh, my.</i>

34:05.551 --> 34:08.168
You are looking the worse
for wear, Gabriel.

34:08.219 --> 34:09.386
You did this.

34:09.422 --> 34:10.838
Well, the drugs helped,

34:10.889 --> 34:13.139
and the power of suggestion,

34:13.175 --> 34:14.591
but uh-huh, it was me.

34:14.592 --> 34:17.594
Did you enjoy yourself?

34:17.596 --> 34:21.648
Mmm, carpe diem has always
been my motto.

34:21.684 --> 34:24.818
But you also proved the point
of our little adventure.

34:24.853 --> 34:26.103
Do you know what it is?

34:26.105 --> 34:28.822
Oh, I wouldn't hazard
a guess.

34:28.858 --> 34:31.824
Well, while your body
may be strong,

34:31.860 --> 34:34.995
your mind is malleable.

34:35.031 --> 34:37.581
It can't take the same rigors
as your physical form.

34:37.616 --> 34:40.083
<i>It will bend to my will.</i>

34:40.119 --> 34:44.755
So I'll break your mind first,
and when that job's done,

34:44.790 --> 34:46.422
I'll take your body.

34:46.458 --> 34:48.125
You won't succeed.

34:48.127 --> 34:50.761
I've always liked
your spirit, Gabriel.

35:06.062 --> 35:07.945
Take what you need.
Destroy the rest.

35:07.980 --> 35:09.897
The helicopter will be
filled to capacity.

35:09.949 --> 35:11.815
When Daria gets here, we leave.

35:18.240 --> 35:22.242
Take your hand off her mouth
or I'll cut it off.

35:33.756 --> 35:35.839
Don't worry.
We'll be home soon.

35:39.678 --> 35:43.013
[labored breathing]

35:47.520 --> 35:50.020
- <i>Claire.</i>
- Is it done?

35:50.022 --> 35:53.190
The Agri-tower is ours,

35:53.192 --> 35:55.526
and the armory on that side
of the trench is destroyed.

35:55.528 --> 35:57.578
- Zoe?
- Captured.

35:57.613 --> 35:59.613
What about David?

35:59.665 --> 36:01.698
He's on the run.
But we'll find him.

36:01.700 --> 36:03.000
It's only a matter of time.

36:03.035 --> 36:06.453
<i>And Arika is on her way
to jail.</i>

36:06.505 --> 36:08.122
Good.

36:11.343 --> 36:12.543
Good.

36:19.185 --> 36:21.468
Claire. Claire.

36:21.520 --> 36:23.804
[sobs]

36:32.198 --> 36:34.531
Leave us.
Lock the door.

36:37.820 --> 36:40.404
Sure you want to be
locked up in here with me?

36:40.406 --> 36:41.572
Even with my bare hands I...

36:41.574 --> 36:42.990
Stop talking.

36:46.495 --> 36:49.463
You and I, we shared
the same dream.

36:49.498 --> 36:51.882
A better life in Vega.

36:51.917 --> 36:54.468
<i>And I gave you
so many chances to join me</i>

36:54.503 --> 36:57.554
but you just lied
and betrayed me.

36:57.590 --> 36:59.223
You're going to
put this on me?

36:59.258 --> 37:00.974
As if it's my fault?
I didn't betray you...

37:01.010 --> 37:03.560
My baby is gone.

37:03.596 --> 37:07.431
And now I have to fight
a war without mercy.

37:07.433 --> 37:11.401
And innocent lives will be lost.

37:11.437 --> 37:14.571
Because of you.

37:14.607 --> 37:16.690
Look, Claire, you're not
the only one to lose, okay?

37:16.742 --> 37:18.158
I'm sorry if you've...

37:18.194 --> 37:19.276
[gunshot]

37:37.880 --> 37:40.214
<i>William: And we feel
we're alone.</i>

37:40.266 --> 37:43.133
<i>Like God's left us.</i>

37:43.135 --> 37:45.385
I did after facing
every horrifying thing

37:45.437 --> 37:47.104
you can imagine.

37:47.139 --> 37:49.273
But I was wrong.

37:49.308 --> 37:52.893
Because He's still here.

37:52.945 --> 37:56.313
And anyone who tells you
different's a liar.

37:56.315 --> 38:00.901
<i>I know because He
revealed Himself to me.</i>

38:01.954 --> 38:05.822
Edward?

38:05.824 --> 38:08.075
Edward.

38:08.127 --> 38:12.296
I was at my lowest point,
blinded by the sun,

38:12.331 --> 38:14.665
skin peeling off my back.

38:14.667 --> 38:17.718
<i>I was approached
by six horsemen.</i>

38:17.753 --> 38:20.170
They were thieves.

38:20.172 --> 38:24.841
They wanted my canteen and a few
strips of dried meat I had.

38:24.843 --> 38:26.760
And there was nothing
I could do to stop them.

38:26.812 --> 38:31.682
But then as the first attacker
came at me,

38:31.684 --> 38:36.403
this blinding flash of light
filled the sky.

38:36.438 --> 38:39.856
It was so bright
it turned night into day.

38:39.858 --> 38:43.110
It was as if a comet
had hit the Earth,

38:43.162 --> 38:44.244
but it was
even greater than that

38:44.280 --> 38:47.281
because this wasn't a comet.

38:47.333 --> 38:49.750
This was the hand of God.

38:49.785 --> 38:52.619
And He was reaching down
from high up there,

38:52.671 --> 38:54.788
and He killed that attacker
stone dead,

38:54.840 --> 38:57.841
right in front of me.

38:57.876 --> 39:01.178
It was a miracle.

39:01.213 --> 39:04.264
God was proving
He was still here.

39:04.300 --> 39:07.968
<i>And that He was
watching out for me.</i>

39:08.020 --> 39:09.686
[coughs]

39:09.722 --> 39:13.724
<i>The horses knew it.
Animals have that sense.</i>

39:13.726 --> 39:17.811
<i>They threw their riders
and took off for the hills.</i>

39:17.863 --> 39:21.064
<i>The rest of the attackers
ran off into the night</i>

39:21.066 --> 39:26.653
and as I lay there, stunned,

39:26.705 --> 39:30.824
something started
to occur to me.

39:30.876 --> 39:35.462
I'd been chosen.

39:35.497 --> 39:38.415
And these...

39:45.758 --> 39:50.677
these are my markings.

39:50.729 --> 39:55.432
Now some of you are innocent,
and some of you are not.

39:55.434 --> 39:58.101
But I am here
to cleanse the evil

39:58.103 --> 40:00.771
within your troubled hearts.

40:05.701 --> 40:08.819
You, boy. Menathas, yes?

40:08.854 --> 40:12.439
Where's your boss?

40:12.441 --> 40:15.609
Did Julian instruct you
not to talk to me?

40:18.414 --> 40:20.998
If you haven't the time
for conversation,

40:21.033 --> 40:25.085
maybe I'll just take
your body for a spin instead.

40:39.635 --> 40:42.803
[groaning]

40:42.838 --> 40:45.139
Nice try.

40:45.141 --> 40:47.474
Ah, you're just
an eight-ball.

40:47.476 --> 40:48.892
Julian told us you might try

40:48.944 --> 40:50.644
<i>to perform your little
puppet show.</i>

40:50.646 --> 40:52.696
He taught us
to resist possession.

40:52.731 --> 40:53.981
But...

40:53.983 --> 40:56.483
[chuckling]

40:56.519 --> 41:02.322
[whistling]

41:05.494 --> 41:08.662
I've had eight-balls
watching you for years.

41:08.664 --> 41:11.498
I knew someday
you'd be my guest.

41:11.500 --> 41:14.418
"Be prepared" is
pretty much my motto.

41:14.470 --> 41:15.719
Among others.

41:15.754 --> 41:18.472
Now where were we?
Oh, yes.

41:18.507 --> 41:21.758
You said that I couldn't break
your mind and take your body,

41:21.810 --> 41:25.145
and as you're so very steadfast
in your resolve,

41:25.181 --> 41:28.482
I've decided to
ratchet things up a notch.

41:35.274 --> 41:38.158
Let's seize the day.

